; to offense. I mostly fish on weekend, too. What I was referring to by weekend warrior trout fishermen are the guys whose total fishing time is a few weekends a year when they fish for just-planted hatchery trout with garlic-flavored marshmallows. Nothing wrong with that in itself either (I've spent MANY a day fishing with marshmallows <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ). But when you combine<br>
<br>
a) the trout stockings and good weather generally align best for these guys during spring, <br>
b) the lakes with planted trout also have trophy bass, and <br>
c) where they fish on the lake puts them in prime view of bedding bass, <br>
<br>
there is a lot of contact between these fishermen and trophy bass on beds. Either by sheer number of anglers throwing marshmallows in their nests, or (very likely) by illegal snagging, many 10+ pound bedding bass are caught and killed every spring by these anglers. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfishtalkandfishingreports.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nico@fishtalkandfishingreports>Nico</A> at: 2/2/03 8:23:46 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfishtalkandfishingreports.showUserPublicProfile?gid=okiebass56>okiebass56</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/2/03 11:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffishtalkandfishingreportsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Here's a sticky Subject!  Bed Fishing?</span><hr size=1> Nico,<br>
<br>
No way personal, I respect you as a fisherman and it is obvious to me you devote your self to it 100%. I've learned a lot from your posts.<br>
<br>
I get a little more perturbed with the spring warriors myself.<br>
Guess we all have our beef.I mean those that get in the weekend warriors way, only they just seem to be there in the spring.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I was accused of raping bedding fish last year by some dude which was totally reticules. The water looked like coffee, I couldn't see a bed if I wanted too and neither could he. I did find some good fish pre and post spawn though, most likely just off the beds. It takes a heck of a lot more talent and patients to coax a trophy bass off the bed than what I was doing and I for one wish you success in your efforts.<br>
<br>
Good fishing to you,<br>
Jerry <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Vernon</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FFFF00>(2/3/03 11:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffishtalkandfishingreportsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~tavrdvssv/Tempphotos/tempphotos/IMAG0004.GIF" align=absmiddle>  Re: Here's a sticky Subject! Bed Fishing?</span><hr size=1> &gt;D Kinda touchie subject, I don't do a lot of bed fishin' but when I lived on the lake I did have the opportunity to watch and fish beddin' bass, what I found was 90% of the fish caught off bed's were male's, the female's tend to do there business at night then are gone. Beside's most big female's spawn in deeper then most guy's fish in the spring. So I'd say if you handle them careful and release them in good shape no problem.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
